==Finnish==

===Etymology===
From Baltic, cf. Latvian ''[[alus#Latvian|alus]]'' "beer, ale". Alternatively from Proto-Germanic ''[[*aluÞ]]'', whose cognates include Swedish [[öl#Swedish|öl]].

===Noun===
'''olut'''

# A fermented beverage made of malt: [[beer]], [[ale]].

